President Obama spoke with Chilean President Sebastian Piñera during the Global Nuclear Security Summit. They discussed various issues on the bilateral, hemispheric, and global agendas. President Obama thanked President Piñera for Chile's recent removal of highly enriched uranium and praised Chile's leadership in promoting nuclear non-proliferation. The two presidents agreed to collaborate on promoting shared values such as democratic governance, human rights, economic prosperity, and social inclusion throughout the Americas. President Obama also offered further assistance to Chile for earthquake recovery if requested by the Chilean government.